      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Line two baking trays with baking paper.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub in butter",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the {{plain-flour}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, {{baking-powder}}, {{ground-ginger}}, ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "mixed spice",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpaefnht00002gv4hs8en9bv"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ", and {{fine-sea-salt}} in a large bowl. Add the cold {{unsalted-butter}} and rub in until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Stir in the {{caster-sugar}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add syrup and form",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm the {{golden-syrup}} briefly in a small saucepan until runny, then add it to the crumb mixture. Mix to a firm dough. Roll into balls the size of a marble, about 15 g each. Place on the trays with plenty of space between them: they spread to roughly twice their raw diameter.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 10 to 12 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Watch from 10 minutes: the biscuits should be spread, golden, and crackling on the surface. They will still feel slightly soft; they crisp up as they cool. Slide the paper off the tray onto a rack and leave the biscuits undisturbed for 5 minutes before lifting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
